SIMPLE: slot
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Slot
<hw>Slot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LG. & D. <ets>slot</ets>
a lock, from a verb meaning to close., to shut, D. <ets>sluiten</ets>;
akin to G. <ets>schliessen</ets>, OHG. <ets>sliozan</ets>, OFries.
<ets>sl<?/ta</ets>, and probably to L. <ets>claudere</ets>. Cf.
<er>Close</er>, <er>Sluice</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A broad, flat,
wooden bar; a slat or sloat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A bolt or bar for fastening a door.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A narrow depression, perforation, or aperture; esp.,
one for the reception of a piece fitting or sliding in it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slot</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Slot
<hw>Slot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Slot</er> a
bar.]</ety> <def>To shut with violence; to slam; <as>as, to
<ex>slot</ex> a door</as>.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slot</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Slot
<hw>Slot</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Icel. <ets>sl<?/<?/</ets>, and E.
<ets>sleuth</ets>.]</ety> <def>The track of a deer; hence, a track of
any kind.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As a bloodhound follows the <qex>slot</qex> of a hurt deer.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sloth</ent>⟦br⟧
